<p align="center"><font color="#0E024D" face="Arial"><strong>PLAYER SUBMITTED STRATEGY</strong></font></p>
<div align="center"><center>

  <div align="center"><center><table border="0" width="90%">
    <tr>
      <td>
      <center><font face="Arial"><strong><b><font color="#800000">TROLL & OGRE SHAMANS. LEVELS 1-7 (THE EASY WAY)</b></font> - <small>Kazbaz, Tunare</small></strong></font><font face="Arial"></center>
<div align="center"><center>
<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="80%">
  <tr>
    <td>
    <small><hr size="1" color="#C0C0C0"><P>
    First of all, get bound outside the entrance to Grobb 
in Innothule swamp if you're an ogre. Believe me, 
you don't want to spend these levels in the Feerrott. 
Getting to Grobb without dying at level one shouldn't 
be too hard, just use one of the many maps online if 
you don't know the way.<P><P>

Don't bother with Rathe Mountains or South Ro, you'll 
just die. Innothule is the way to go. 

From lvl 1 to lvl 4, fight right near the entrance to 
Grobb, so you can run to the Bashers if you need to. 
Fight snakes to get snake scales for the Snake Skin 
Spell you get at 5th level. Stock up now, when snakes 
are still worth xp. Fight skeletons for bones, rusty 
weapons and a cracked staff. (decent newbie weapon) 
Turn 4 bones in to the Shadow Knight leader in Grobb 
for rusty two-handed. 16 bones = 1 plat from the shops 
for the swords. Do this over and over.<P>
Do not fight young water moccassins even if they con 
blue unless you like healing up all the poison damage. 
Once they con green, kill 'em for snake scales. Regular 
water moccassins leave large snake scales, which can't 
be used for the spell. Otherwise, kill anything that 
cons white or blue. Be careful about lesser kobolds, 
they gang up one you and wander. Froglok tads leave 
netted armor, so kill as many as you can. Save some 
flesh too, put it in the bank or something.<P><P>
Once you hit lvl 5, you'll have to move a bit. Only 
the lesser kobolds will still con blue. Walk north 
along the East zone wall until you start to see 
frogloks. If you see one, pull it as close to the wall 
as you can, because frogloks gang up hard, and you
are less likely to attract a gang this way. Avoid 
froglok fisherman until they con blue. (white if they're 
alone and you can pull them to a wall Even then, 
you're risking a major gang-up)<P>
Give 1 froglok meat and 2 froglok flesh to the Warrior 
leader in Grobb for rusty two-handed axe. They're 
worth the same as the swords, so 1 plat for every 4 
froglok meats and 8 froglok fleshes. By the time you 
hit lvl 6, you should have 10 plat in the bank, at 
least. You'll have start venturing farther along the 
zone wall as you get up in levels. At level 7, you'll 
have to fight near the entrance to upper guk because 
only fisherman, foragers and guards will still con blue. 
I advise fighting in a group here, I've seen gangs of 
12 or more froggies. Running into the guk zone is the 
only way to escape a gang unless you're sowed, so get 
the hang of that and watch out for people running the 
other way, because there's a steady stream of trains 
out of guk. :)<P>
Also, from lvl 4-7 look for giant rats and swamp 
alligators. These are easy kills, even if white, and 
they're great xp. You might even solo a yellow. 
Again, pull them to a wall, or you'll be ganged up on 
by froggies or the fungus man trackers, which are good 
kills if you can catch them alone. Trackers will still 
be blue at lvl 8, but they're not as common.<P>
Even if you're a troll and have regen, save your mana 
for buffs and heals, but if you're at full mana, 
Sicken is a decent spell to start off with. For soloing, 
Drowsy is a good first attack, but in general, healing 
is more efficient use of mana at these levels. At lvl 
8, things get complicated, since there isn't 
a smooth transition to your next hunting area. 
More on that in the 8-15 strategy. 
Alternate ways to go: If you're grouped, go hunt 
lizardmen camps east of the river in Feerott at lvl 6. 
At lvl 8, you'll still need to move on though.<P><P>

Good luck, and by the way, with this method getting to 
lvl 6 takes 5 hours or less, assuming you don't die 
too often. Re-memorizing spells is a pain until you 
get those spell skills up. It was frustratingly slow 
for me until lvl 8 when I took the time to max out my 
spell skills. At lvl 8, you also get meditate, which 
more than doubles your mana regen.<P>
Getting from 6-8 is another good 3-4 hours, because 
of the inherent danger fighting frogloks of being 
gangbanged. Assuming you were in a group, or really 
cautious about pulling, you can do it in 3. Worst 
case scenario, 5 hours. So, you could get lvl 8 in 
less than 8 hours of play. In my case it took 10, 
because I was learning these lessons the hard way. :)
<P><P>
Kazbaz of Tunare.
    </small></font></p>
    <p><small><font face="Arial">&nbsp;</font></small></td>
